metadata.name: Scream
metadata.description:
In the beginning, there was only chaos. A swirling maelstrom of energy and matter, unformed and undirected. And from the chaos emerged a deity, a being of pure anarchy and destruction. This deity was known as Maruna.

Maruna reveled in the turmoil she caused, tearing apart worlds and civilizations with reckless abandon. Her very presence was enough to shatter reality and bring about the end of all things. Those who worshipped her did so out of fear, offering sacrifices in the hopes of placating the deity's insatiable hunger for destruction.

Despite her fearsome reputation, Maruna was not without its own vulnerabilities. It was said that the deity could be bound by powerful magic, and that she could be defeated by those who wielded the power of order and unity. But such individuals were rare, and Maruna continued to spread its influence across the universe, leaving a trail of devastation in its wake.
